                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2660: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-29T12:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1922—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received November 30—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. Your telegram number 30, November 28, 7 p.m. Cable as received does not show
                    what law is meant. Electoral law not yet promulgated. Commission has been in
                    session at the Legation for the past ten days and the law will probably be in
                    condition for publication within a week or ten days but will not be promulgated
                    by the Provisional Government until the people have had the opportunity to
                    criticise and suggest changes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
